6. Adverbs of comment - Explore adverbs for telling stories

strangely
Strangely, there was nobody at home.

suddenly
Suddenly, I felt cold air coming from the kitchen.

The speaker is surprised that there was nobody at home.
The adverb "strangely" suggests that it was unexpected and difficult to understand.

The cold air came quickly and in an unexpected way.

Adverbs of comment
Adverbs of comment usually go at the beginning of a sentence before a comma (,).

They help us understand what the speaker thinks.
Strangely, she was late for the meeting.
The event was unexpected and difficult to understand. 

Suddenly , I felt cold air .

obviously
Obviously, Keith left the window open again.

Surprisingly
Surprisingly, the door to the garden was wide open.

obviously - the speaker expected it
surprisingly - the speaker didn't expect it

unfortunately
Unfortunately, nobody answered.

gradually
Gradually, I started to realise something wasn‚Äôt right.
"Gradually" suggests that it happened little by little.

immediately
Immediately, I decided to run out of the house.
"Immediately" suggests that he did it without thinking.

Match the opposites.
obviously - suddenly
strangely - gradually

It was past 6pm. Strangely, there was nobody at home. 
Keith was not having his afternoon tea in the living room, 
as he usually does at this time, and Jasper, our dog, 
was not running around excited to see me. 
Suddenly, I felt cold air coming from the kitchen.

"Obviously, Keith left the window open again. 
It's the middle of winter, for God's sake," I thought to myself angrily. 
Surprisingly, it wasn't the window. The door to the garden was wide open. 
But I couldn‚Äôt see anybody. 
I was beginning to have bad feelings about all of it. 
I called ‚ÄúKeith, Jasper! Are you there?‚Äù I waited and then called again.

Unfortunately, nobody answered. The whole place was silent. 
Even the neighbours were unusually quiet. 
Gradually, I started to realise something wasn‚Äôt right. 
Then I noticed two broken plates on the kitchen floor. 
Immediately, I took my bag and the car keys and decided to run out of the house. 
But as I was reaching for the front door I felt a heavy hand pulling me back inside.

The house seemed empty.
The window was closed.
He started feeling afraid.
Immediately, he decided to leave the house.

