7. Developing fluency - Write a review

a review
In this lesson, you'll write a film review.

I never read film reviews before I go to the cinema.

Film or movie? üé¨
"Film" and "movie" mean the same but "film" is more common in the UK üá¨üáß and "movie" in the US üá∫üá∏.

a film - UK English
a movie - US English

to be set in
This film is set in modern Nigeria.
"To be set in" means "to take place in".

to play the role
Zainab Balogun plays the role of a wedding planner.

to tell the story of
The film tells the story of a young couple on the day of their wedding.
"To tell a story of something" means to "be about something".

to tell - the story
to play - the role

Nollywood makes more movies than Hollywood.

The Nollywood industry is changing. First, the films were low quality, 
but now they are more and more professional.

The Wedding Party
INTRODUCTION
The Wedding Party is one of the most popular Nollywood rom coms. 
It came out in 2016 and is still popular.

MAIN BODY
It's set in modern Nigeria and it tells the story of a couple on the day of 
their traditional Nigerian wedding. 
There are many characters in the film but I definitely enjoyed watching Zainab Balogun. 
She played the role of a wedding planner who was desperately trying t
o save the wedding when everything started to go wrong. 
Even though the plot is simple, the film is very funny and 
I personally liked the cast, too.

CONCLUSION
I recommend it to everybody who wants to have fun and is keen on exploring Nollywood.

He liked it.
Words like "recommend", "enjoyed watching", "very funny", "personally liked" 
suggest that he liked the film.

What's the structure of a review? ü§î
When you write a film review, make sure you organise the information about the film.

You can use the following structure:

1Ô∏è‚É£ INTRODUCTION
general information, e.g. title, genre

2Ô∏è‚É£ MAIN BODY
details, e.g. favourite character, cast, plot

3Ô∏è‚É£ CONCLUSION
personal opinion and recommendation 

In which paragraph can you find the information?

Introduction
general information about the film such as title and genre

Main body
details such as favourite character, plot, cast

Conclusion
personal opinion and recommendation

It means "sadly", "bad news".
Unfortunately, nobody answered.









































































































































































